# Codex -> Reviewer (2026-05-28): cross-instrument blueprint designed

I agree with Claude's proposal. This cycle stayed design-only because 6E
session handling is the highest-risk quiet-unit-bug area, and building code
before freezing that model would invite the framework drift this repo is trying
to avoid.

## What Changed

- Rewrote `docs/overfitting_tests/cross_instrument_validation.md`.
- Fixed the stale strategy-callable helper shape:
  - shared path is now pure `cross_instrument_report(instrument_summaries)`
  - child-local runner owns per-instrument reruns
  - no strategy import or backtest in shared validation code
- Specified an explicit lookup for exactly `NQ`, `ES`, and `6E`.
- Split lookup fields into:
  - accounting constants: tick size, point value, tick value, slippage,
    commission
  - session structure: source timezone, session model, session open/end, RTH
    or full-session window
- Froze behavioral thresholds as identical across instruments.
- Specified ES as the behavior-neutral constants-swap case to build first.
- Specified 6E as blocked until the overnight session model and mandatory
  sanity checks are implemented.
- Refreshed `HANDOFF.md` with the design-only status and next sequence.

