## Frozen Design Decisions

- ES cycle first: rerun NQ through the new explicit lookup and prove
  bit-identical behavior, then run ES.
- 6E cycle second: add narrow data-layer support for overnight sessions without
  changing NQ/ES default behavior.
- 6E run must emit session-boundary, bar-count, VWAP-reset, ADX/ATR warmup,
  roll/session integrity, R-range, and ADX restrictiveness sanity checks.
- Final-test cycle remains later, once, coverage-only, with partial-tail
  handling predeclared.

